## 3. ENVIRONMENT SETUP

### Install Runtime Dependencies

```bash
uv sync
```

### Install with Development Dependencies

```bash
uv sync --all-groups
```

Installs pytest, ruff, mypy, pre-commit, and build tools.

**⚠️ MANDATORY:** Always run `uv sync` after modifying any `pyproject.toml`.

---

## 4. TESTING

### Run Full Test Suite

```bash
uv run pytest -q
```

Runs all tests across all packages with coverage tracking.

### Run Specific Package Tests

```bash
uv run pytest tests/packages/indexed-core/ -q
uv run pytest tests/packages/indexed-config/ -q
uv run pytest tests/apps/indexed_app/ -q
```

### Run with Coverage Report

```bash
uv run pytest -q --cov=src --cov-report=html
```

View report at `htmlcov/index.html`.

### Test Organization

- `tests/apps/indexed_app/` - CLI application tests
- `tests/packages/` - Individual package tests
- `tests/integration/` - End-to-end tests
- `tests/fixtures/` - Shared test data

---

## 5. CODE QUALITY (ruff)

[ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) handles linting, formatting, and import sorting across the entire monorepo.

### Run Linter

```bash
uv run ruff check .
```

### Auto-Fix Issues

```bash
uv run ruff check . --fix
```

Fixes unused imports, whitespace, line length, and import sorting issues.

### Format Code

```bash
uv run ruff format
```

### Quality Workflow

```bash
uv run ruff check . --fix
uv run ruff format
uv run ruff check .
```

### Configuration

Configured in root `pyproject.toml`:
- **Line length:** 100 characters
- **Target Python:** 3.11+
- **Rules:** F (Pyflakes), E (pycodestyle errors), W (warnings), I (isort)

---

## 6. TYPE CHECKING (mypy)

```bash
uv run mypy src/
```

Check entire monorepo or specific packages.

